We need to determine who is a knight and who is a knave among six inhabitants: Joe, Bob, Ted, Zippy, Alice, and Zoey. Each person makes a statement, and we need to determine the truth values of these statements to identify the knights (who always tell the truth) and knaves (who always lie).

